;Jack's Office

NUMBER 1683
NAME Field of Corn
PLAIN
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand amidst an endless field of corn. Tall cornstalks stand in neat rows, as if awaiting marching orders in some vegetable conflict. The sky above is clear and empty, except for a flock of ravens circling far overhead. In the center of the cornfield an empty post rises above the level of the growing corn. A discarded sign lays half-buried in the rows of corn.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1076 ADJ1=355
EXTEND 0 rising above the stalks of corn
ITEM 1 936 adj1=665
ITEM 2 204 adj1=88 adj2=355
EXTEND 2 laying discarded in a plowed furrow
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
This old weathered sign has obviously seen better days. In fact, it has probably seen more useful ones. it lays half-buried in a plowed furrow, serving no purpose as far as you can tell.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB READ 2
 ECHO OTHERS %n bends over to read a half-buried sign.
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
 	ECHO PLAYER    Jack's Secret Script Instructions...
 	ECHO PLAYER       (Proceed at your own risk.)
 	ECHO PLAYER ----------------------------------------------
 	ECHO PLAYER 1)Set JACKGUILD to a guild number to find
 	ECHO PLAYER   all on-line members.
 	ECHO PLAYER 2)Set WERECHECK to 1 to check for all online
 	ECHO PLAYER   werewolf players.
 	ECHO PLAYER 3)Set TANNSPELLS to playernum for a barrage
 	ECHO PLAYER   of helpful magic.
 	ECHO PLAYER 4)Set TANNWRATH to playernum and TANNCRIT to
 	ECHO PLAYER   1-7 for a gruesome death.
 	ECHO PLAYER 5)Set TANNROOM to a room number and TANNMOVE
 	ECHO PLAYER   to a player number to move player via runes.
 	ECHO PLAYER 6)Set TANNRUME to a room number and TANNSHOW
 	ECHO PLAYER   to a playernumber to show a room to someone.
 	ECHO PLAYER 7)Set JACKAGER to a player number to check
 	ECHO PLAYER   someone's age, or set JACKAGE to change it.
 	ECHO PLAYER 8)Set TANNCHECK to a player number to check
 	ECHO PLAYER   the level of lyncanthropy in a player, or
 	ECHO PLAYER   their lichness or Teiwaz/Aelfen totem.
 	ECHO PLAYER 9)Set TANN57 and TANN98 to values, and TANNUM
 	ECHO PLAYER   to a player number to change those INTNUMs.
 	ECHO PLAYER 10)Set JACKRACE to a player number to check
 	ECHO PLAYER    a player's race.
 	ECHO PLAYER ----------------------------------------------
 ELSE
 	ECHO PLAYER The nearly illegible writing reads, "kEEp oUT! tHIs MeANs YOU %N!!!".
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;Carriage stuff!!!
INUMBER 1227
NAME 1201
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 1000
SUBSTANCE INDESTRUCTABLE
PORTAL

IFPREVERB GO -1
 CLEARVERB
 AFFECT 3450
 IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
  AFFECT CARRIAGEROOM
  IFVAR WEALTH >= 1000
   DISBAND
   SUB WEALTH 1000
   ECHO PLAYER You climb into the carriage and pay 10 gold coins to the driver.
   ECHO OTHERS %n climbs into the carriage.
   MOVE 3450
   AFFECT 3450
   ECHO OTHERS %n climbs into the carriage.
   ECHO PLAYER The driver says, "Please, take yer seat."
  ELSE
   AFFECT CARRIAGEROOM
   ECHO PLAYER You try to climb into the carriage...
   ECHO OTHERS %n tries to climb into the carriage...
   ECHO ALL The driver says, "Sorry, you don't have enough to cover the ride."
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  AFFECT CARRIAGEROOM
  ECHO PLAYER You try to climb into the carriage...
  ECHO OTHERS %n tries to climb into the carriage...
  ECHO ALL The driver says, "Sorry, no more room this trip."
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB EXAMINE -1
 CLEARVERB
 SHOWROOM 3450
ENDIF


NUMBER 3450
NAME Carriage
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This four-wheeled, horse-drawn carriage is constructed out of hand-carved white wood. Two seats face each other behind a high driver's perch. No roof or covering obscures the view from within the carriage. A garland of roses is woven through the rear of the carriage, giving the whole a festive air. A freshly cut, longstemmed rose has been placed on each seat and a small gate in the side leads out.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;Items
;2 seats
ITEM 0 339 ADJ1=239 ADJ2=738
ITEM 1 339 ADJ1=239 ADJ2=738
;driver (man)
ITEM 2 1587
EXTEND 2 sitting on the driver's perch
;roses are an IFENTRY/NEWPUT string
ITEM 3 862 ADJ1=294

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The plush velvet cushions on this bench look extraordinarily comfortable. The bench faces forward, towards a similar one, facing in reverse.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The plush velvet cushions on this bench look extraordinarily comfortable. The bench faces backwards, towards a similar one. ALong the edge of the cushions you notice a series of tiny mythological figures embroidered in gold thread. The only two you don't readily recognize are what appear to be a scarecrow and a puppet, who seem to be endlessly chasing each other in a circle.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The driver is a mature man, white beard and hair showing beneath an imposing top hat. His clothing is formal and dignified, a tuxedo over a ruffled shirt and black bow-tie.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 3
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR POSITION ! 0
  ECHO PLAYER You must stand first.
 ELSE
  DISBAND
  ECHO PLAYER You step out of the carriage.
  ECHO OTHERS %n steps down from the carriage.
  MOVE CARRIAGEROOM
  AFFECT CARRIAGEROOM
  ECHO OTHERS %n steps down from the carriage.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GAZE -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You gaze out of the carriage at the street beyond...
 SHOWROOM CARRIAGEROOM
 ECHO OTHERS %n gazes out of the carriage at the street beyond.
ENDIF

IFENTRY
 IFIN 0 277 -1
  EQUAL DUMMY4 0
 ELSE
  NEWPUT 0 274 ADJ1=1226 ADJ2=259
 ENDIF
 IFIN 1 277 -1
  EQUAL DUMMY4 0
 ELSE
  NEWPUT 1 274 ADJ1=1226 ADJ2=259
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB LISTEN -1
 ECHO PLAYER You hear the gentle clip clop of the horses hooves, and the sweet jingling of its harness bells.
ENDIF

IFVERB SMELL -1
 ECHO PLAYER You inhale the heady scent of the rose garland.
ENDIF

IFSAY ADVENTURER'S_GUILD?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "The Adventurer's Guild? I hear tell it's a good place for young folks to start learnin' a trade."
ENDIF

IFSAY THE_CRIMSON_BAND?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "They're supposed to be in charge of the army of the King, but all I ever see them do is have parties and beat each other senseless in their private arena."
ENDIF

IFSAY BANK?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "The bank here in Fayd is just about the best place to put your hard earned gold."
ENDIF

IFSAY BAZAAR?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "The bazaar is the social center of Fayd. Heck, just about everyone seems to sit around here most of the time."
ENDIF

IFSAY POOR_QUARTER?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Ach! That section of town is a blight on the rest of us. The miscreants who run the place are more dangerous than a whole herd of kobolds."
ENDIF

IFSAY RANDOLPH'S?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Randolph is the finest jeweler in town, although I think sometimes he just a bit too big for his britches."
ENDIF

IFSAY FLOWERS?
 ECHO ALL The little flower shack on Park is the best place in all of Andor to buy the most beautiful flowers."
ENDIF

IFSAY THE_LAST_RESORT?
 ECHO ALL It's supposed to be some sort of secret, but the members of that club tend to be misfits and eccentrics. They all live in that big house on Park."
ENDIF

IFSAY CHURCH_STREET?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Church Street is home to all of the town's recognized temples. Lots of places for prayer and such, if your in need of any."
ENDIF

IFSAY KEY_'N_ANCHOR?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Yep, the Key 'N Anchor is Fayd's newest business, started by some seafaring knave and his lockpickin' friend."
ENDIF

IFSAY GARIN?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Mr. Garin is Fayd's current mayor, a fine upstanding man, even if it's hard to tell if he's up-standing or down-sitting."
ENDIF
IFSAY KORAZON?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "That's that fella that the mayor ran outa town... or so I hear it. No one has seen him since Garin was elected. Makes ya wonder."
ENDIF

IFSAY THALION?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Sir Thalion is the Paladin of Shemri, I hear tell. Although, I've never met a more suspicious acting paladin in all my days."
ENDIF

IFSAY LINNEAUS?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Linneaus Wanderfar? Supposed to be some hot-shot mage, but I think he just tells folks that to meet more ladies.?
ENDIF

IFSAY SIERRON?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "That dried up old husk of an undead guy? Thinks he's scary, but looks to me like a good stiff breeze'll blow him away."
ENDIF

IFSAY SHANE?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Shane's the owner of the town saloon. Nice please, but I think the house cheats in the gambling room."
ENDIF

IFSAY SALOON?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "The saloon is just off the bazaar, not a bad place for a soak, a drink, or a spot of gamblin'"
ENDIF

IFSAY MOULIN?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Moulin? Ain't he that fella who's gettin' all the aelves stirred up about their ancient totem lore? Seems a bit silly if you ask me."
ENDIF

IFSAY BROOK?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Ack! Don't ask me about that lunatic healer! Last time he was on my carriage he tried to kiss me! On the lips!"
ENDIF

IFSAY PROPHET?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "He's one o' them drakin fellas what started the Way isn't he? Frankly, knowin' my family there's no way I'd go for ancestor worship."
ENDIF

IFSAY CYRANO?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "He's a hot-shot Crimson Band fella. Supposedly he protects the King and family, but frankly I never see em doin' anything but dressin' up, struttin' around and playin' games in that arena of theirs."
ENDIF

IFSAY CAMORRA?
 ECHO ALL The driver says, "Oh the Duchess. Quite a lady if you ask me, although I wouldn't want to be on her bad side. Seen her skewer some poor sap in the back once. He never knew what hit 'im!"
ENDIF

