REGION 9
CHANNEL 993
OUTOFBODY
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You rest upon the intersection of a giant skein of magical energy which spans this alien place from as far as you can sense. Vast beings of incredible stature move by in the distance on incomprehensible errands. The strands of the web appear as cable-like filaments of energy, varying in color from deep indigo to a rich violet. They run in all directions, intersecting and crossing each other in a pattern which agonizingly remains just out of your perception.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
; EQUAL LICHFULL 47
 PLREVENT 5
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER The web beneath you pulses with energy, which seemingly strenghtens your being.
 PLREVENT 15
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER You feel more aware of yourself with every passing moment.
 PLREVENT 15
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER Something immense beyond comprehension seems to lurk just out of the range of your perceptions.
 PLREVENT 5
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER You become convinced the immense being is somehow taking inventory of your worth.
 PLREVENT 15
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER A surge of energy pulses through the web in your area, and you notice the immense being is no longer present.
 PLREVENT 15
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO PLAYER In the tangle of energies, you discern that with a small tug here... and a quick twist there...
 SPELL 352 99
 EQUAL MANAPOINTS 52
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 ECHO PLAYER You no longer sense the realm of the web.
 POSITION STAND
 MOVE LICHROOM
; EQUAL LICHFULL 0
 AFFECT LICHROOM
 ECHO OTHERS The dust on the ground rises up to solidify into %n.
ENDIF
;
;**This is the archtype for the Lich Diadem... which
;**combined with an intnum57 value of -47 defines
;**the player as a lich. Macro20 contains the RoomX scripts
;**which provide periodic monitoring of lich attributes.
INUMBER 1458
NAME 652
ARMOR
WEIGHT 2
VOLUME 3
SUBSTANCE INDESTRUCTABLE
PARAMETER1 70
WORN_HEAD
LIGHTABLE
*DESCRIPTION_START
The diadem is formed from an unbroken band of darkest metal. It is smooth and cool to the touch, forming a perfect circle, except for the single deep red gemstone which gleams from its front.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;GM warning
IFVERB LOOK -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
  ECHO PLAYER ***This is a special archtype of the diadem, useable only by liches. For further information please contact Jack Fetch, at 1-800-STRAW MAN.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LIGHT -1
 CLEARVERB
 SUB MANAPOINTS 2
 ECHO PLAYER You focus mana through your eye sockets, creating the illusion of ghostly, glowing orbs there.
 ECHO OTHERS Briefly, a pair of ghostly, glowing eyes appear in the gaping sockets of %n's skull.
 SPELL 520 99
 PLREVENT 0
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO OTHERS The ghostly eyes in %n's skull slowly fade away.
 ECHO PLAYER The ghostly eyes in your skull slowly fade away, leaving your vision unchanged.
ENDIF

;Keeps non-liches away from item.
IFTOUCH -1
 IFVAR INTNUM57 ! -47
  CLEARVERB
  STRCVT 0 PLAYERNUM
  DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 225 A blast of violet magical energy rips through you as you touch %a!
  ECHO OTHERS As %n touches %a, it releases a blast of violet energy which rips through %h body!
  GMMSG **%n (PLAYERNUM %0) is messing with a lich's diadem... might want to take a peek.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;Head Glue
IFPREVERB REMOVE -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You cannot seem to pull %a from your brow.
 ECHO OTHERS %n fidgets with %a on %h brow, restlessly.
ENDIF
;**Effects (no real impact)
IFPREVERB TAP -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You shift your weight, causing your bones to crack and rattle.
 ECHO OTHERS %n shifts from side to side, and the sound of cracking and rattling bones fills the air.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SMELL -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER A scent like the stale, still air of a long buried tomb wafts forth from your skeletal frame.
 ECHO OTHERS A scent like the stale still air of a long buried tomb wafts forth from %n's skeletal frame.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RAISE -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You lean forward inquisitively.
 ECHO OTHERS %n leans forward inquisitively.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You allow yourself to hold the magic in the very air, causing your eye sockets to glow with a deep red light.
 ECHO OTHERS %n's empty eye sockets begin to glow with a deep red light.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB EAT -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You absentmindedly gnash your teeth with a dry scraping sound.
 ECHO OTHERS A dry scraping sound issues forth from %n's bony jaws.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB WAVE -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You recall the moment of your final death, reliving each moment of your passing.
 ECHO OTHERS A chill shadow falls over the area, bringing with it the scent of the grave.
ENDIF
;**Impacts (yet still effective)
;knock everyone down and stun them (in roomx)
IFPREVERB RUB -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You trace a pattern onto the surface of your diadem.
  ECHO OTHERS %n reaches up, as if to reassure %iself that %h diadem is still worn.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER Your eye sockets seem to burn with an intense wave of energy.
  ECHO OTHERS %n's empty eye sockets glow a vivid shade of orange.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The very ground seems to ripple and waver as if it has lost some basic physical attribute.
  EQUAL LICHSHAKERM RNUM
  SUB MANAPOINTS 75
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;phantom form
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You reach out mentally to the essence of your diadem, enfolding yourself in the darkness at its heart.
  ECHO OTHERS %n fades away, leaving only the lingering image of a skull with red, glowing eye sockets.
  IFVAR MANAPOINTS > 39
   SPELL 248 99
  ENDIF
  SUB MANAPOINTS 40
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;freeze room
IFPREVERB TICKLE -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You run your fingers over the diadem in a fluttering pattern.
  ECHO OTHERS %n raises %h hands to %h head for a moment.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You feel your magical energy gathering the the sockets of your skull, then flowing forth into the atmosphere around you.
  ECHO OTHERS The empty sockets in %n's head glow an eerie blue, which seems to almost flow outwards from %i.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  IFVAR NIGHT = 1
   ECHO ALL The temperature drops to dangerously low levels!
   DAMAGEALL COLD 32 A rime of frost appears on %n!
  ELSE
   ECHO ALL The temperature drops dramatically, causing you to shiver.
  ENDIF
  SUB MANAPOINTS 55
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;summon creature
IFPREVERB TURN -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You turn the diadem slightly on your head.
  ECHO OTHERS %n readjusts %h diadem.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You feel a strange sensation as a warped life energy gathers within your skull.
  ECHO OTHERS A sickly green light erupts from %n's gaping eye sockets.
  PLREVENT 3
  CONTPLREVENT
  IFVAR NIGHT = 1
   EQUAL RITUALVAL2 182
   SPELL 2 99
   ECHO PLAYER A skeletal figure claws its way up through the ground to stand before you.
   ECHO OTHERS The figure stands before %n as if awaiting %h commands.
   SUB MANAPOINTS 34
  ELSE
   EQUAL RITUALVAL2 1
   SPELL 2 99
   ECHO PLAYER A skeletal figure claws its way up through the ground to stand before you.
   ECHO OTHERS The figure stands before %n as if awaiting %h commands.
   SUB MANAPOINTS 24
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;Healing
IFPREVERB PINCH -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You gently grasp the diadem, calling upon it to channel you the energy you require.
 ECHO OTHERS %n grasps %h diadem and his eye sockets glow with a gentle violet light.
 PLREVENT 0
 CONTPLREVENT
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SPELL 337 99
 SUB MANAPOINTS 35
ENDIF
;teleport to crypt
IFPREVERB THUMP -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You trace out a rune in the air with a skeletal finger.
  ECHO OTHERS %n traces out a rune in the air with a skeletal finger.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The rune hangs in the air, in burning red lines of energy.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The rune seems to grow and expand, encompassing you in its fiery embrace!
  DAMAGEALL BURN 3 The heat sears %n as it passes over %h body!
  SUB MANAPOINTS 25
  IFVAR RNUM ! 3461
   EQUAL LICHGROUPRM RNUM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
    AFFECT 3461
    ECHO ALL A flash of red light sharply illuminates some figures appearing out of thin air!
   ELSE
    AFFECT 3461
    ECHO ALL A flash of red light sharply illuminates the form of %n, as %s appears out of thin air!
   ENDIF
   AFFECT LICHGROUPRM
   MOVEALL 3461
  ELSE
   IFVAR LICHGROUPRM ! 0
    IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
     AFFECT LICHGROUPRM
     ECHO ALL A flash of red light sharply illuminates some figures appearing out of thin air!
    ELSE
     AFFECT LICHGROUPRM
     ECHO ALL A flash of red light sharply illuminates the form of %n, as %s appears out of thin air!
    ENDIF
    AFFECT 3461
    MOVEALL LICHGROUPRM
    EQUAL LICHGROUPRM 0
   ELSE
    IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
     AFFECT 66
     ECHO ALL A flash of red light sharply illuminates some figures appearing out of thin air!
    ELSE
     AFFECT 66
     ECHO ALL A flash of red light sharply illuminates the form of %n, as %s appears out of thin air!
    ENDIF
    AFFECT 3461
    MOVEALL 66
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  ECHO ALL The rune fades, leaving you somewhere else.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;provide user information
IFVERB RECALL -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = -47
   ECHO PLAYER You realize that if you turn it, you will summon aid.
   ECHO PLAYER If you tickle it, you will lower the temperature.
   ECHO PLAYER If you rub it, you will cause the area to shift and waver.
   ECHO PLAYER If you concentrate upon it, you will fade out of view.
   ECHO PLAYER Pinching it will replenish your physical being.
   ECHO PLAYER Thumping it will take all to the crypt of Phule del Luna.
   ECHO PLAYER You also sense that all of these powers are costly...
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3461
NAME The Crypt of Phule del Luna
DEEPCAVE
channel 132
REGION 9
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand within a tomb, deep underground in some unknown location. The air is still and musty with the ages, hinting at untold years unspoiled by the breath of man. An ornate sarcophagus fills the center of the crypt, adorned with ancient carvings. Next to it, a stone throne rises up on a small dias, overlooking the dusty chamber. A giant slab of marble fills what was once a door to the chamber, effectively sealing it off from the outside world.
A shelf along one wall holds a collection of valuable looking jars along with a large, leather manuscript which is secured with silver chains. An unusual crystal rests upon a wooden stand.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;sarcophagus
ITEM 0 234 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=312
EXTEND 0 covered in ornate carvings
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The sarcophagus is covered entirely in carvings which seem to detail the life of a mighty ancient king or leader of some sort. In a few of the pictures, you see him standing in front of a vast multitude casting some sort of strange spells into the air, leading you to believe that he also had some magical powers.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;throne
ITEM 1 542 ADJ1=652 ADJ2=187
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
This throne is large and massive, carved from a single gigantic block of black marble. It rises above the floor on a raised dais, giving the occupant a good view of the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;shelf
ITEM 2 277 ADJ1=312
EXTEND 2 high on the left wall of the room
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
You see a long shelf, firmly attached at human chest height to the left wall of the chamber. Upon it rest several jars, and a large manuscript.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;manuscript
ITEM 3 202 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=180 ADJ3=1414
EXTEND 3 secured by a silver chain
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
This book seems rather well constructed as it has lain here for centuries without deteriorating completely. The heavy leather cover bears a single word, "Kharuman".
*DESCRIPTION_END
;slab
ITEM 4 1599 ADJ1=189 ADJ2=187
EXTEND 4 blocking the exit from the crypt
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The marble slab seems to be at least fifteen feet wide and ten feet high. From the way the bedrock floor seems to sag beneath its weight, you would guess that you cannot budge it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;jars
ITEM 5 356
EXTEND 5 made of red clay
ITEM 6 356
EXTEND 6 made of blue glass
ITEM 7 356
EXTEND 7 made of green veined porcelain
ITEM 8 1277 ADJ1=145 ADJ2=340
EXTEND 8 on a dark wooden stand
;
IFPREVERB GAZE 8
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You gaze deeply into %a.
 ECHO OTHERS %n gazes deeply into %a.
 IFVAR INTNUM57 = -47
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You see a vision deep within the crystal.
  ECHO OTHERS A strange violet light is reflected in %n's empty eye sockets as it washes out of the crystal.
  SHOWROOM LICHGROUPRM
  AFFECT LICHGROUPRM
  ECHO OTHERS A cold violet light, briefly illuminates the area.
 ELSE
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You see nothing at all.
  ECHO OTHERS %n looks bewildered.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 5
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You attempt to place %a in a jar.
 ECHO OTHERS %n attempts to place %a in a jar.
 IFVAR ARCHNUM ! 118
  ECHO ALL It does not fit.
 ELSE
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 < 100000
   ECHO ALL The jar seems to repel %a strangely.
  ELSE
   IFVAR LICHRITUAL = 0
    ECHO ALL %A falls into the jar easily, which begins to glow with a strange reddish light.
    ADD LICHRITUAL 1
    REMOVEITEM -1
   ELSE
    ECHO ALL The jar is already full.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 6
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You attempt to place %a in a jar.
 ECHO OTHERS %n attempts to place %a in a jar.
 IFVAR ARCHNUM ! 512
  ECHO ALL It does not fit.
 ELSE
  IFVAR ITEMADJ3 ! 1104
   ECHO ALL The jar seems to repel %a strangely.
  ELSE
   IFVAR LICHRITUAL = 1
    ECHO ALL %A falls into the jar easily, which begins to glow with a strange blueish light.
    ADD LICHRITUAL 1
    REMOVEITEM -1
   ELSE
    ECHO ALL The jar is already full.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 7
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You attempt to place %a in a jar.
 ECHO OTHERS %n attempts to place %a in a jar.
 IFVAR ARCHNUM ! 1370
  ECHO ALL It does not fit.
 ELSE
  IFVAR ITEMADJ3 ! 292
   ECHO ALL The jar seems to repel %a strangely.
  ELSE
   IFVAR LICHRITUAL = 2
    ECHO ALL %A falls into the jar easily, which begins to glow with a strange reddish light.
    ADD LICHRITUAL 1
    REMOVEITEM -1
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL The sarcophagus thrums slightly with an eldritch power.
   ELSE
    ECHO ALL The jar is already full.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN 0
 IFVAR LICHRITUAL < 3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot budge the heavy lid.
  ECHO OTHERS %n strains at the lid of the sarcophagus.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
 IFITEM 0 CLOSED
  ECHO PLAYER It is closed.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You climb within the narrow sarcophagus.
  ECHO OTHERS %n climbs within the narrow sarcophagus.
  POSITION LAY
  IFVAR LICHRITUAL = 3
   EQUAL LICHRITUAL 4
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL A green-violet glow fills up the sarcophagus, nearly blinding you with it's brilliance.
   PLREVENT 2
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER You feel magical forces tugging and pulling at your soul.
   ECHO OTHERS The sarcophagus' interior is completely concealed by the brilliant glow.
   PLREVENT 3
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER Your life force seems to drain from your body completely, leaving you a lifeless husk. As you fade, you notice a diadem laying within the sarcophagus.
   ECHO OTHERS The glow fades away rapidly, revealing %n laying motionless.
   IFVAR INTNUM57 = 0
    IFVAR MANAPOINTS > 350
     EQUAL INTNUM57 -47
     NEWPUT 0 1458 ADJ1=287 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=118 VAL2=15
    ELSE
     DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 227 The magical forces at your command are not great enough to complete the ritual.
     ECHO OTHERS %n writhes in pain, but nothing happens.
    ENDIF
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Your werewolf blood somehow resists the forces at work, leaving you healthy.
    ECHO OTHERS The shadowy form of a wolf appears around %n for a moment.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ 3
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR LICHPAGE = 0
  ECHO PLAYER The cover of the book reads, "Kharuman".
 ENDIF
 IFVAR LICHPAGE = 1
  ECHO PLAYER The first legible page details the life and times of Kharuman, King of Kings, who ruled with a vast army and great magical powers at his command. From some of the incidents, you can easily assume that he did not necessarily rule with the acclaim of his subjects.
 ENDIF
 IFVAR LICHPAGE = 2
  ECHO PLAYER Further into the manuscript, you read of Kharuman's quest for knowledge arcane. Apparently he searched for what he termed, "The Elixer of Life". Worried that his life was coming to an end, Kharuman searched through every method at his disposal for a mysterious substance that would allow him to hang on to his mortal existance.
 ENDIF
 IFVAR LICHPAGE = 3
  ECHO PLAYER In Kharuman's handwriting you read, "Ist myraculous seen of the mae miteculous formulae. Tae bae nah elixir of all, mae ist be ine irtual arcanne. Forst ay bae securen ine stohn surpassen beutie in redden collor for jarren forst."
 ENDIF
 IFVAR LICHPAGE = 4
  ECHO PLAYER The handwriting continues, "Seyond, ist dae dussen frae ine rohk do fallen haevanfrommen. Dae dussen belonnen ein dae seyond jarren."
 ENDIF
 IFVAR LICHPAGE = 5
  ECHO PLAYER The second to last page of the manuscript is torn and frayed, revealing only the words, "dae mettallen essen putte ein dae faenel jarren."
 ENDIF
 IFVAR LICHPAGE = 6
  ECHO PLAYER The final page of the manuscript only says, "Nae Kharuman gaes tae dae haeyer raellem."
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN 3
 CLEARVERB
 ADD LICHPAGE 1
 IFVAR LICHPAGE < 7
  ECHO PLAYER You turn the page of the manuscript.
  ECHO OTHERS %n turns the page of the manuscript.
 ELSE
  EQUAL LICHPAGE 0
  ECHO PLAYER You close the manuscript again.
  ECHO OTHERS %n closes the manuscript again.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

;Werewolf collar

INUMBER 958
NAME 55
WEIGHT 3
VOLUME 3
ARMOR
SUBSTANCE SOFTMETAL
ENCRUSTABLE
WORN_NECK
*DESCRIPTION_START
The collar is made from interlapping scales of leather, edged in hard metal, which form staggered rows all around its circumference. A clasp in the shape of a wolf claw holds it shut.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFTOUCH -1
 EQUAL ITEMVAL2 2
 IFVAR INTNUM98 < 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Something about the collar keeps your hand away.
  ECHO OTHERS %n reaches for %a, but something seems to hold %i away.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR INTNUM98 > 60
  IFVAR NIGHT = 1
   ECHO PLAYER You reach within yourself and tap the power of the wolf.
   ECHO OTHERS %n's eyes gleam with a reddish glint.
   SPELL 536 99
  ELSE
   IFVAR INTNUM98 > 75
   ECHO PLAYER You reach within yourself and tap the power of the wolf.
   ECHO OTHERS %n's eyes gleam with a reddish glint.
   SPELL 536 99
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You try to touch the wolf within, but cannot seem to reach it.
    ECHO OTHERS %n's eyes gleam with faint hint of red.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You bare elongated canines.
 ECHO OTHERS %n bares unusually elongated canines.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER You cast about in the air for a scent.
 ECHO OTHERS %n casts about in the air as if scenting something.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR INTNUM98 > 95
  IFVAR REGION = 0
   IFNOITEM 9
    ECHO PLAYER You draw upon your connection with the hallowed werewolf grove, and form a trail through the aether.
    ECHO OTHERS %n's eyes glow with a fiery red light, and a trail appears leading out into thin air.
    NEWITEM 9 410
    SETITEMVAL 9 2 2250
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 18
    PLREVENT 5
    ECHO ALL The trail fades away into nothingness.
    REMOVEITEM 9
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You cannot seem to do that here.
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER The grove is too far away to reach from here.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR INTNUM98 > 90
  IFVAR REGION = 0
   ECHO PLAYER You draw upon your connection with the hallowed werewolf grove, and follow it's beckoning call through the aether.
   ECHO OTHERS %n's eyes glow with a fiery red light, and %s vanishes.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER The grove is too far away to reach from here.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CAST -1
 IFVAR INTNUM98 > 50
  ECHO PLAYER Your inner eye follows the call of the werewolf grove...
  SHOWROOM 2250
  ECHO OTHERS %n's eyes seem to reflect a dull red gleam for a moment.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
 IFVAR INTNUM98 > 0
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER You realize that the collar will enable several werewolf abilities as time goes on.
  ECHO PLAYER You can transform by concentrating upon it.
  ECHO PLAYER You can push or pull for effect.
  ECHO PLAYER More advanced werewolves can cast to view the werewolf grove.
  ECHO PLAYER Mature werewolves can go through the collar to reach the werewolf grove,
  ECHO PLAYER and they can open it to create a path for others.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;MACRO STUFF
VARIABLE JACKMACRO
VARIABLE ILZARTIMER
VARIABLE ILZARPAIN
VARIABLE ILZARPAINC
VARIABLE ILZARANDOM

MACRO 20
;Ilzar ROOMX stuff.

IFVAR ILZARPAIN ! ILZARTIMER
 IFVAR ILZARPAINC > 99
  EQUAL ILZARPAINC 0
 ENDIF
 IFVAR ILZARPAINC = 0
  EQUAL ILZARPAINC PLAYERNUM
 ELSE
  IFVAR REGION = 5
   IFVAR ORG ! 14
    IFVAR ORG ! 23
     IFVAR ORG ! 1
      IFVAR MANAPOINTS > 0
       SUB MANAPOINTS 25
      ENDIF
      IFVAR PSIPOINTS > 0
       SUB PSIPOINTS 25
      ENDIF
      ECHO PLAYER The dark atmosphere seems to press down upon you.
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   RANDOM ILZARANDOM 1 30 0
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 1
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER From somewhere in the city, a terrible cry of pain rings out.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 2
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER You hear an ululating cry from the top of the pyramid.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 3
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER The faint smell of incense reaches you from the bulk of the dark cathedral.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 4
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER A pair of attendants from the temple of Shin-Jah drag a terrified slave past you.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 5
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER The dark cathedral suddenly glows with a violet light from every window.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 6
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER Several dark shadows drift slowly over the city like tiny stormclouds, except for the fact that they move against the wind.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 7
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER You hear the creaking of a wagon's wheels, accompanied by the a low moaning, as it bears its load of prisoners along.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 8
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER A pair of silent dour children scurry past on some unknown errand.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 9
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER The sharp tangy scent of fresh blood wafts in on the breeze.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 10
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER A trio of slaves appear with scrubbing implements, and begin scouring a bloodstain on the pavement.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 11
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER You hear the sound of a spell being prepared.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 12
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER Tendrils of inky black mist creep along the ground at knee level, as if seeking something.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 13
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER You hear the sharp crack of a whip, followed by a wordless grunt of pain, from somewhere nearby.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 14
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER From the mountainsides above the city, you hear the mournful cries of wolves echoing back and forth.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 15
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER You feel a chill down your spine, as if someone had just stepped on your grave.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ILZARANDOM = 16
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER A pair of acolytes drag a lifeless body down the street.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ILZARPAINC = PLAYERNUM
   EQUAL ILZARPAINC 0
   EQUAL ILZARPAIN ILZARTIMER
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

;********Lich script*********
;LICH SHAKING POWER ACTIVATE!
IFVAR LICHSHAKERM ! 0
 IFVAR LICHSHAKEC = 0
  EQUAL LICHSHAKEC PLAYERNUM
 ELSE
  IFVAR RNUM = LICHSHAKERM
   IFVAR INTNUM57 ! -47
    IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
     POSITION LAY
     ADD ROUNDTIME 10
     DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 4 The shifting floor throws you to the ground!
     ECHO OTHERS %N loses %h balance and falls to the ground!
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR LICHSHAKEC = PLAYERNUM
   EQUAL LICHSHAKERM 0
   EQUAL LICHSHAKEC 0
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR LICHCOUNTER = 0
 EQUAL LICHCOUNTER 1
ENDIF
IFVAR LICHCOUNTER = PLAYERNUM
 ADD LICHCOUNT 1
ENDIF
IFVAR INTNUM57 = -47
;check for death
 IFVAR DEAD = 1
  IFVAR RNUM ! 3460
   ECHO PLAYER As you lay upon the cold hard ground, your corporeal shell crumbles back into the dust it came from.
   ECHO OTHERS %n's corpse collapses in upon itself with a sigh, leaving only a pile of dust in its wake.
   EQUAL LICHROOM RNUM
   MOVE 3460
   IFNOITEM 9
    NEWITEM 9 512
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 3460
   ECHO PLAYER You find yourself losing track of the physical realm, and drift in a realm of pure, dark magical energy.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
;check undead status
 IFVAR UNDEAD ! 1
  IFVAR DEAD = 0
   ECHO PLAYER A swirling tempest of black magical energy erupts from your living, beating heart, erupting from your chest with brutal force!
   ECHO OTHERS A gout of black swirling energy rips its way from %n's chest, leaving %h body in tatters.
   EQUAL BODYPOINTS 1
   DAMAGEPLR ELECTRIC 75 You feel as if you are being ripped apart by the savage blast of energy!
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
;check mana number
 IFVAR MANAPOINTS < 0
  IFVAR DEAD = 0
   ECHO PLAYER Your mana reserves are exhausted, leaving you no energy with which to hold your decaying body together!
   EQUAL BODYPOINTS 1
   DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 40 The very atmosphere crushes your frail shell of a body.
   ECHO OTHERS %n virtually implodes, %h bones and skin collapsing inward with a rush of air!
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
;perform routine lich functions: magic cost, ????
 IFVAR LICHCOUNT > 19
  EQUAL LICHCOUNT 0
  IFVAR DAY = 1
   IFVAR OUTDOOR = 1
    SUB MANAPOINTS 12
   ELSE
    SUB MANAPOINTS 8
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   SUB MANAPOINTS 4
  ENDIF
 ;holy ground
 ;Rorin's Temple
  IFVAR RNUM > 1189
   IFVAR RNUM < 1195
    DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 13 The sanctity of this place causes you to writhe in agony!
    ECHO OTHERS %n is wracked by a shuddering spasm.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  ;Amilor's Temple
  IFVAR RNUM > 590
   IFVAR RNUM < 594
    DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 13 The sanctity of this place causes you to writhe in agony!
    ECHO OTHERS %n is wracked by a shuddering spasm.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  ;Shemri's Temple (entrance only...)
  IFVAR RNUM = 333
   DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 13 The sanctity of this place causes you to writhe in agony!
   ECHO OTHERS %n is wracked by a shuddering spasm.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;********end lich***********
;A stray Teiwaz script
IFVAR TEIWAZBELL ! 0
 IFVAR TEIWAZBC = 0
  EQUAL TEIWAZBC PLAYERNUM
 ELSE
  IFVAR INTNUM98 = 0
   IFVAR INTNUM57 > 0
    IFVAR INTNUM57 < 11
     ECHO PLAYER You hear a distant note, soft yet all-pervasive in tone. Your vision clouds for a moment and you see:
     SHOWROOM 2437
     ECHO PLAYER You realize that you have been summoned.
     ECHO OTHERS %n pauses for a moment, as if listening to something.
     GMMSG ** %n was just summoned to the Teiwaz Tree.**
     AFFECT 2437
     ECHO ALL Briefly, reflected in the vibrating plate, you see the face of %n.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR TEIWAZBC = PLAYERNUM
   EQUAL TEIWAZBC 0
   EQUAL TEIWAZBELL 0
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;--------------------------------------
;- Tiewaz Tree Challenge Stuff & Stuff |
;--------------------------------------

IFVAR RNUM = 2438
 IFVAR TCHALLENGE > 1
  IFVAR MONINROOM < PLRSINROOM
   ADD TCHALLENGE 1
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVAR RNUM = 2438
 IFVAR TCHALLENGE = 5
  IFCARRY 1861 -1
   ECHO PLAYER A wizened elder emerges from the shadows of the chamber and exchanges shrouds with you.
   ECHO OTHERS A wizened elder emerges from the shadows to exchange shrouds with %n.
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 50
    SETITEMVAL -1 5 50
   ELSE
    IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 100
     SETITEMVAL -1 5 100
    ELSE
     IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 200
      SETITEMVAL -1 5 200
     ELSE
      ECHO ALL You notice that the new shroud is identical to the old.
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER A wizened elder emerges from the shadows to greet you with a smile.
   ECHO PLAYER He places a white shroud on the floor, bows toward you and disappears into the shadows once again.
   NEWITEM 4 1861 ADJ1=347
   SETITEMVAL 4 1 INTNUM3
   ECHO OTHERS A wizened elder emerges from the shadows to greet %n with a smile.
   ECHO OTHERS He places a white shroud on the floor, bows toward %n and disappears into the shadows once again.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVAR RNUM = 2438
 IFVAR TCHALLENGE = 10
  EQUAL TCHALLENGE 0
  ECHO PLAYER A guard escorts you out of the chamber.
  ECHO OTHERS A guard escorts %n out of the chamber.
  MOVE 2437
 ENDIF
ENDIF

;;-----------------------------------
;;- TANNRUME is the room to be shown |
;;- TANNSHOW should equal PLAYERNUM  |
;;-----------------------------------
;
;IFVAR PLAYERNUM = TANNSHOW
; ECHO PLAYER You get a strange tingle as you receive a vision...
; SHOWROOM TANNRUME
; ECHO OTHERS %n gets a far off look for a moment.
; EQUAL TANNSHOW 0
; STRCVT 0 TANNRUME
; GMMSG ** %n was just shown room #%0.
;ENDIF
;
;---------------------
;-Lycanthropy Factors |
;---------------------

IFVAR NIGHT = 1
 IFVAR INTNUM98 ! 0
  IFVAR RAC < 7
   ADD INTNUM57 1
   IFVAR INTNUM57 >= 200
    EQUAL INTNUM57 0
    IFVAR OTHERFORM ! 1
     IFVAR DEAD ! 1
      IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
       RANDOM DUMMY4 1 100 10
       IFVAR DUMMY4 >= INTNUM98
        ECHO PLAYER The moonlight catches your eye sending a shiver down your spine...
        ECHO OTHERS %n raises %h eyes and stares trancelike into the silvery moonlight.
        STRCVT 1 PLAYERNUM
        GMMSG ** %n, Player #%1, is feeling the effects of lycanthropy.
        SPELL 536 0
        SPELL 535 0
        ECHO PLAYER You feel your blood coursing through your veins, your senses become more alert and for some reason everything seems taller.
       ELSE
ECHO PLAYER The moonlight catches your eye and your heartbeat quickens.
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ELSE
     IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
      IFVAR INTNUM98 < 50
       SPELL 535 0
       STRCVT 3 PLAYERNUM
       GMMSG ** %n, player #%3 is stuck in wolfform keptain!
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVAR INTNUM98 ! 0
 IFVAR INTNUM57 = 2
  IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER The moon transfixes you...
     ECHO PLAYER You stand motionless, dazzled before its beauty.
     ECHO OTHERS %n raises %h head and stares motionless at the moon in utter amazement.
     ADD INTNUM57 1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVAR INTNUM98 ! 0
 IFVAR INTNUM57 = 2
  IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
    IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
     ECHO PLAYER The moon transfixes you...
     ECHO PLAYER You stand motionless, dazzled before its beauty.
     ECHO OTHERS %n raises %h head and stares motionless at the moon in utter amazement.
     ADD INTNUM57 1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVAR INTNUM98 ! 0
 IFVAR INTNUM57 = 6
  IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
   IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
    SPELL 518 0
    SPELL 534 0
    ECHO PLAYER Your claws glow an eerie red and you feel the power of the moon channel through your lupine body!
    ECHO OTHERS %n howls and raises %h head to the sky!
    ADD INTNUM57 1
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVAR INTNUM57 = 107
 IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
  IFVAR OUTDOOR = 0
   RANDOM TANNECHO 1 12 0
   IFVAR TANNECHO = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You suddenly feel... alive!
    ECHO PLAYER The light of the moon caresses you, it makes you wish to run with it.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR TANNECHO = 2
    ECHO PLAYER You catch the faint scent of prey somewhere nearby...
    ECHO PLAYER You can practically feel the beating of a living heart.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR TANNECHO = 3
    ECHO PLAYER As the moon catches your eye once again you feel the sudden urge to sink your fangs into living flesh.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR TANNECHO = 4
    ECHO PLAYER You feel the sudden urge to raise your head and cry to the moon!
   ENDIF
   IFVAR TANNECHO = 5
    ECHO ALL The moon become exposed as the clouds before it drift apart.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR TANNECHO = 6
    ECHO OTHERS %n raises %h head and cries to the moon!
    ECHO PLAYER The moon comes into full view from behind the clouds and your heartrate quickens!
    ECHO PLAYER You let loose a cry to the moon!
    EQUAL WEREROOM RNUM
    IFVAR EXITN ! -1
     AFFECT EXITN
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
    IFVAR EXITNE ! -1
     AFFECT EXITNE
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
    IFVAR EXITE ! -1
     AFFECT EXITE
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
    IFVAR EXITSE ! -1
     AFFECT EXITSE
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
    IFVAR EXITS ! -1
     AFFECT EXITS
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
    IFVAR EXITSW ! -1
     AFFECT EXITSW
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
    IFVAR EXITW ! -1
     AFFECT EXITW
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
    IFVAR EXITNW ! -1
     AFFECT EXITNW
     ECHO ALL You hear the song of a wolf crying to the moon nearby!
     AFFECT WEREROOM
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
